  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0332">
<l>ṉakāra viṟuti valleḻut tiyaiyiṉ</l>
<l>ṟakāra mākum vēṟṟumaip poruṭkē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Scholars say that - as mentioned above -<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">Mēr kiḷant(u)aṉṉa ;</foreign> cf. 248, accord. to
          which these nouns take the empty morph <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṉ.</foreign></note></l>
<l>words [ending in <foreign xml:lang="ta">-m</foreign> and] denoting days</l>
<l>take the [empty morph] <foreign xml:lang="ta">attu</foreign> before <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṉ</foreign></l>
<l>and the consonant [<foreign xml:lang="ta">m</foreign>] disappears.<note
              place="foot">e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">makam + pōyiṉāṉ &gt; makat-tārpōyiṉāṉ</foreign> (i.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta"> maka + attu + āṉ)</foreign> ' he went on the day of the 10th lunar asterism '.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
